    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a pristine example of Zuffenhausen engineering, featuring the 3.6L M96/03 flat-six powerplant with VarioCam Plus. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering power through a mechanically sound limited-slip differential. This vehicle has undergone a comprehensive IMS bearing retrofit with a ceramic solution, ensuring long-term structural reliability. The chassis remains exceptionally taut, utilizing its original multi-link rear suspension geometry and MacPherson front struts, while the braking system features four-piston aluminum monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history, the factory Lapis Blue Metallic paint retains its deep luster, and the cockpit exhibits zero bolster wear or dashboard UV degradation. A turn-key collector-grade machine for the discerning purist.",
      "price": 46500.0,
